Product Id: Historical quarterly data are available in the archived table 32-10-0337.
Inventories can also be found in table 32-10-0160.
January to June, the beginning inventory is dated January 1.  July to December, the beginning inventory is dated July 1.
The pig crop represents the number of live piglets after weaning.
Other disposition principally represents slaughter on a province of origin basis and may include hogs destined for export; varies by province.
January to June, the ending inventory is dated July 1. July to December, the ending inventory is dated January 1 of the following year.

Beginning in January to June 2017, estimates of interprovincial movements are derived from PigTRACE data and have been adjusted using random tabular adjustment, to protect respondent confidentiality. A quality measure (A, B, C, D, or E) has been assigned to the estimate to indicate the degree of confidence users can have in its accuracy.
